h1. Description

Issues with a custom 'checkbox' field cannot be transitioned through the transition screen in Bitbucket.
h1. Steps to reproduce

1. Set up a jira project that has required fields on transition
 2. Add a custom field of type 'checkbox' to a jira project.
 3. Mention the Jira ticket in Bitbucket and try to transition it
h2. Expected come

Issue transitions without problems
h2. Actual outcome

No errors show on the transition dialog but transition does not appear to succeed. 
 The network tab shows that the transition request contained a field called 'undefined', and the response from Jira is a 500.

Request:
{code:java}
          "postData": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "text": "{\"fields\":{\"customfield_10007\":{\"name\":\"khughes\"},\"fixVersions\":[{\"id\":\"10000\"}],\"assignee\":{\"name\":\"khughes\"},\"undefined\":[],\"resolution\":{\"id\":\"10000\"}},\"transition\":{\"id\":\"41\"}}"
          }   {code}
Response:
{code:java}
            "text": "{\"errors\":[{\"context\":\"undefined\",\"message\":\"Field 'undefined' cannot be set. It is not on the appropriate screen, or unknown.\",\"exceptionName\":null}]}"
          },  {code}

 Bitbucket logs show the following error:
{code:java}
2018-05-25 16:00:25,921 ERROR [http-nio-7990-exec-1] admin @ACFO9Wx960x360x0 15m1395 0:0:0:0:0:0:0:1 "POST /rest/jira-integration/latest/issues/TEST-1/transitions HTTP/1.1" c.a.i.i.jira.DefaultJiraService TEST-1 could not be transitioned: JiraErrors{errorMessages=[], errors={undefined=Field 'undefined' cannot be set. It is not on the appropriate screen, or unknown.}}
{code}

There are a lot of these logs on the bitbucket AU mirror:
{noformat}
2017-06-02 02:21:37,776 ERROR [threadpool:thread-4] upstream_8dc0bb6c-b31b-3d96-8835-eea2516116bd @IXAGBDx1356x13x0 v3jm7m 192.168.1.1,127.0.0.1 "POST /rest/mirroring/latest/upstreamServers/8dc0bb6c-b31b-3d96-8835-eea2516116bd/addon/events HTTP/1.1" c.a.b.i.m.m.s.DefaultMirrorSynchronizationHelper stash/PROJ/repo: failed to prepare local repository: The repository has been moved to STASH/ACET/dbr-preprocessing-pipeline-old
{noformat}
It seems like the mirror doesn't gracefully handle repository moved exceptions.

h3. Problem Definition
Upon using *PreRepositoryHook* veto message from this hook is not propagate a custom error message from the hook when committing file via the UI(online editor), the JS does not permit to pass any message from the hook. This is due to the code for commit-dialog.js has hardcoded only one message:
{noformat}
webapp/default/src/main/frontend/static/bitbucket/internal/feature/file-content/edit/commit-dialog/commit-dialog.js
{noformat}

This somehow rather falls back to printing the default errors:
{code:java}
AJS.I18n.getText('bitbucket.web.sourceview.edit.error.forcePR.message'),
AJS.I18n.getText('bitbucket.web.sourceview.edit.error.branchPermission.title')
{code}

h3. Suggested Solution
Propagated the custom error message from the hook when committing files via the online editor in Bitbucket Server UI.

h5. {color:#333333}Summary{color}

On the Commits page of Bitbucket Server 5.10 , hovering over the tag labels shows the tag name tooltip and the commit message tooltip.
h5. {color:#333333}Steps to reproduce{color}
 # Make a commit by editing a file directly in Bitbucket Server UI file browser.
 # Click on the commit *commit hash* in the Commit page of the BItbucket Server UI and add a Tag to the commit .
 # Hover over the commit hash in the commits page. 
 # Hover over the tag tooktip.

h5. {color:#333333}Expected Behavior{color}

Either the tag name tooltip or the commit message tooltip should be shown, depending on which the user hovers over.
h5. {color:#333333}Actual Results{color}

Hovering over the tag labels shows the tag name tooltip and the commit message tooltip.

h3. Summary
The filter usage on the {{PERMISSIONS/USERS}} REST API endpoints is incorrect.


h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Access the REST API documentation at https://docs.atlassian.com/bitbucket-server/rest/latest/bitbucket-rest.html for the following endpoints:
## {{GET /REST/PROJECTS/\{PROJECTKEY\}/PERMISSIONS/USERS?FILTER}}
## {{GET /REST/PROJECTS/\{PROJECTKEY\}/PERMISSIONS/USERS/NONE?FILTER}}
## {{GET /REST/PROJECTS/\{PROJECTKEY\}/REPOS/\{REPOSITORYSLUG\}/PERMISSIONS/USERS?FILTER}}
## {{GET /REST/PROJECTS/\{PROJECTKEY\}/REPOS/\{REPOSITORYSLUG\}/PERMISSIONS/USERS/NONE?FILTER}}


h3. Expected Results
The documentation says the following:
{quote}
if specified only user names containing the supplied string will be returned
{quote}

h3. Actual Results
The documentation says the following:
{quote}
if specified only group names containing the supplied string will be returned
{quote}

When using {{server.require-ssl=true}} to trigger HTTP->HTTPS redirects, the following error is logged during startup:
{noformat}
2018-04-24 09:35:42,741 ERROR [localhost-startStop-1] o.a.c.c.C.[Tomcat].[localhost].[/] For security constraints with URL pattern [/status] only the HTTP methods [GET] are covered. All other methods are uncovered.
{noformat}

_This "error" is completely harmless. The setup it's describing is present by design._ The {{/status}} endpoint is often used as a health check URL for load balancers and proxies, which often consider a redirect to be an "unhealthy" response. Since the {{/status}} endpoint doesn't return anything "sensitive" about the instance (an example response is below), even with {{server.require-ssl=true}} the system allows {{/status}} to be accessed via plain HTTP. _All HTTP methods on all other URLs will redirect from HTTP to HTTPS._ Prior to Bitbucket Server 5.8 {{/status}} only allowed {{GET}} requests. 5.8 added support for {{HEAD}} and {{OPTIONS}} requests, which are also _intentionally_ available via plain HTTP.

To avoid unnecessary concern, security constraints should be explicitly configured for all HTTP methods on {{/status}}. Otherwise the error gives the appearance that security constraints haven't been configured correctly.

Example {{/status}} response:
{code}
{"state":"RUNNING"}
{code}

h5. {color:#205081}Problem Definition{color}

When a new Branch is created, there is an option to select Custom type for Branch Type. But when creating  Branch Permission, based on Branch model, Custom type is not displayed as Branch type.
h5. {color:#205081}*Suggested Solution*{color}

There should be Custom type (for permission on all Custom type branch at a go) for branch type when creating branch permission based on branching model. 
h5. {color:#205081}Workaround{color}

Create Branch permission based on Branch pattern or Branch name.

I have created a plugin that has the goal of squashing Repository Deletes.

The code for this plugin is as follows:
{code:java}
import com.atlassian.bitbucket.event.repository.RepositoryDeletionRequestedEvent;
import com.atlassian.bitbucket.i18n.I18nService;
import com.atlassian.plugin.spring.scanner.annotation.imports.ComponentImport;
import com.atlassian.event.api.EventListener;

import org.slf4j.Logger;
import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;

import javax.inject.Inject;
import javax.inject.Named;

@Named
public class DeleteRepositoryBlocker {
    private static final Logger log = LoggerFactory.getLogger(DeleteRepositoryBlocker.class);

    private final I18nService i18nService;

    @Inject
    public DeleteRepositoryBlocker(@ComponentImport I18nService i18nService) {
        this.i18nService = i18nService;
    }

    @EventListener
    public void onDeletionRequested(RepositoryDeletionRequestedEvent event) {
        if(!event.isCanceled()) {
            event.cancel(i18nService.createKeyedMessage("block.deletes.blocked"));

            log.info("{}: repository deletion was blocked by BlockDeleteRepository plugin", event.getRepository());
        }
    }
}
{code}

This code works perfectly for all versions of Bitbucket 4.8.\* - 4.14.\* and when the plugin is active there is a popup message that says that the delete was blocked by the plugin.

This code works perfectly in versions of Bitbucket 5.0.\* - 5.6.5 the same as it does for Bitbucket 4.\* with the popup message that says the delete was blocked by the plugin.

However starting at Bitbucket 5.7.0 and all version after that including the latest version 5.9.1 when the Delete repository button is pressed, the warning dialog to confirm is displayed but when confirmation is given, the screen just flashes.  The repository is not deleted and that is correct, but the popup message is not displayed saying why the repository was not deleted and when in DEBUG logging mode the following can be found in the logs

